# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker build context excludes
#
# Everything here is irrelevant to the API runtime image. Keeping them
# out shrinks context-send time on every build (faster CI) and prevents
# dev secrets / test data / source maps / bundler caches from ever
# ending up in the image layer.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Version control
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Node
**/node_modules
**/npm-debug.log
**/.npm
**/.pnpm-store

# Build outputs — the build stage produces fresh ones
**/dist
**/build
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/.vite
**/coverage

# Tests — not needed in the runtime image
**/__tests__
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/vitest.config.*
**/playwright.config.*
**/e2e
**/test-results
**/playwright-report

# IDE / editor
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Environment files — injected at runtime, never baked in
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.production.example

# Logs
**/*.log
logs

# Docs — not needed in the runtime image
docs
*.md
!README.md

# Web package — Vercel builds and hosts this, not Railway
packages/web/src
packages/web/public
packages/web/dist
packages/web/*.html
packages/web/vite.config.*
packages/web/index.html
packages/web/.vite

# Misc
.claude
.cursor
.github
ACQUISITION_CLOSEOUT.md
